Reference: AI-writing idiosyncrasy taxonomy
-------------------------------------------
The bundled novelist skill cites the LAMP-corpus taxonomy of AI-writing tics:
arXiv:2409.14509. This is a citation only; no text from the paper is bundled.

Typewriter key sounds
---------------------
The five WAVs under assets/sounds/ are CC0 (public-domain) recordings, embedded
in the binary and played on each keypress. For this app they were trimmed to
~0.22-0.25 s, converted to mono 16-bit 44.1 kHz WAV, and peak-normalized to
about -3 dBFS.

  key-click-1.wav, key-click-2.wav, key-click-3.wav
    "Typewriter - single key - type 1/2/3" by yottasounds, from the
    "typewriter" pack on Freesound:
      https://freesound.org/people/yottasounds/sounds/380138/  (type 1)
      https://freesound.org/people/yottasounds/sounds/380137/  (type 2)
      https://freesound.org/people/yottasounds/sounds/380136/  (type 3)
    License: CC0 1.0, https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/

  key-deep-1.wav  "Typewriter, space" (#2843)
  key-deep-2.wav  "Typewriter, Key" (#2842)
    Hermes Precisa 305 recordings by Joseph Sardin, BigSoundBank:
      https://bigsoundbank.com/typewriter-space-s2843.html
      https://bigsoundbank.com/typewriter-key-s2842.html
    License: CC0 / public-domain equivalent, https://bigsoundbank.com/licenses.html

CC0 requires no attribution; the credits above are provided as a courtesy.
